Getting Started with Django

Installing Prerequesites

  • Homebrew 
    ruby -e "$(curl -fsSkL raw.github.com/mxcl/homebrew/go)"
brew doctor
  • Brew Packages 
    brew install git readline sqlite gdbm 
brew install python --universal --framework
  • Pip 
    easy_install pip 
pip install virtualenv

Setting up a dev environment

You should add a couple basic packages to requirements.txt: django, south, django-debug-toolbar 
virtualenv env
source ./env/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
chmod +x manage.py
./manage.py startproject 
./manage.py startapp
